article.headline: New Hampshire 73, Maine 68
article.story: ORONO, Maine (AP) -- Mike Christensen scored a career-high 28 points to help New Hampshire snap a seven-game losing streak against Maine with a 73-68 victory Saturday night. Christensen also had six rebounds and four assists to lead the Wildcats (4-10, 1-1 America East). Blagoj Janev and Jermaine Anderson each scored 17 for UNH, which trailed by five at halftime. Kevin Reed led Maine (5-9, 0-2) with 23 points and nine rebounds. Chris Bruff added 13. The Wildcats came out firing in the second half, scoring the first nine points. A 12-3 scoring run turned a 39-38 New Hampshire lead with 16:53 to play into a 10-point lead with 12 1/2 minutes left. The Wildcats' lead grew to 12 with 9 1/2 minutes to go, but the Bears went on a 10-0 run fueled by five points from Bruff and five straight scoreless possessions by New Hampshire. Free throws -- made and missed -- helped the Wildcats take a 68-58 lead. The Black Bears missed four of five from the line, while the Wildcats hit five of six during that span.
